Introduction

The script run_analysis.R executes the 5 steps described in the course project's definition.

First, all the data are imported into R environment. The cbind/rbind methods are used to bind 'training and test dataset.

Secondly, the select statement inside 'dplyr' package is used to select all column - with names contains 'std' or 'mean'

Thirdly, the mutate function is used to reset the Activity values - based on the dataset - activity_labels

The 4th step: no code is required, because line 27 to line 28 code inside step 1 has already processed the logic

The final step:
ddply statement is used to calculate the means functions based in 'Activity/Subject' groups)



